Genome-wide DNA methylation profiling in the superior temporal gyrus reveals epigenetic signatures associated with Alzheimer's Disease	GSE76105	genetics	Epigenetic - Methylation; Illumina HumanMethylation450 BeadChip	Alzheimer's Disease; Non-demented Controls	68 participants	https://discover.alzheimersdata.org/catalogue/datasets/ceb04cb1-8f6d-468f-b8d5-7816aefb9df2	Strong FAIR compliance with publicly accessible genome-wide methylation data deposited in NCBI GEO (GSE76105) using standardized Illumina HumanMethylation450 BeadChip platform and MIAME-compliant metadata. Data is provided in standard GEO SOFT formats with both raw (IDAT) and processed data files available. The study employs controlled vocabularies and is indexed in major databases (GEO, PubMed, NCBI) with comprehensive methodology documentation. Reusability is supported through detailed sample annotations including age, gender, ethnicity, and tissue characteristics. Findability could be enhanced through DOI assignment and additional cross-repository registration for optimal discoverability.	2026-01-01 00:00:00	Mette	['https://discover.alzheimersdata.org/catalogue/datasets/ceb04cb1-8f6d-468f-b8d5-7816aefb9df2', 'https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/geo/query/acc.cgi?acc=GSE76105']	Study			{'https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/geo/query/acc.cgi?acc=GSE76105': {'https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC10767856': ['27008011', 'PMC8628444', '10.1038/s41576-019-0150-2&amp', '10.1093/bib/bbv011', '10.1093/nar/gkab1030', 'PMC8728269', '10.1016/j.ygeno.2021.08.012&amp', '10.1038/ng1201-365&amp', '10.1093/bib/bbv011&amp', '34850941', '37933855', 'PMC6515678', 'PMC4652617', '10.1093/nar/30.1.207&amp', '10.2202/1544-6115.1027&amp', '10.1038/s41467-017-00025-5', '10.1038/sdata.2016.18&amp', '17496320', '10.1038/s41467-018-03751-6&amp', '10.1038/s41576-019-0150-2', '10.1186/s12967-019-1899-y', '23193258', '10.1126/science.1162228', '10.1093/nar/gkaa762&amp', '10.2202/1544-6115.1027', 'PMC4944384', 'PMC7605509', '10.1186/s13059-