The collaborative St. Jude Children's Research Hospital - Banner Sun Health Research Institute Alzheimer's Disease and Related Dementias Study	StJude_BannerSun	clinical, proteomics	Clinical assessments; Proteomics; Neuropathological data	Alzheimer's Disease; Related Dementias	100 samples	https://www.cell.com/neuron/fulltext/S0896-6273(19)31058-X	Good FAIR compliance with rich multi-modal data (clinical, proteomics, and neuropathological) from established institutional repositories. The Banner Sun Health Research Institute operates a well-characterized brain and body donation program with standardized protocols. However, findability is limited due to lack of a dedicated public study portal, and accessibility likely requires formal data access applications through controlled-access repositories (dbGaP, NIAGADS) or institutional review. Metadata documentation and interoperability standards are uncertain without repository confirmation. Standard data sharing agreements and ethical approval requirements typical for human genomic and tissue data apply.	2026-01-01 00:00:00	Mette	['https://www.cell.com/neuron/fulltext/S0896-6273(19)31058-X']	Study			
