osppsych.2025.03.011', '10.1016/j.archger.2024.105502', '10.1037/hea0001544', '10.3390/nu16040518', '10.3390/nu15061505', '10.3389/fragi.2025.1501168', '10.1093/geront/gnae139', '10.1186/s12877-025-06337-2', '38356730', '36821643', '38565592', '10.1016/S2666-7568(24)00046-1', '10.1093/gerona/glae136', '10.1101/2025.02.03.25320261', '10.1177/09567976241242037', '38702609', '10.1017/S0033291724001272', '10.1007/s40520-025-03179-1', '10.1038/s41598-025-04093-2', '10.1016/j.bbih.2024.100776', '10.1186/s12966-025-01725-8', '10.1371/journal.pone.0280029', '10.1016/j.jdent.2025.105947', '10.1038/s41375-025-02822-0', '37967661', '10.1002/alz.70950', '10.1080/13607863.2025.2468408', '10.1093/eurpub/ckaf132']}}
The Neurodegeneration Pseudotime (DiseasePseudotime) Study		transcriptomics, longitudinal	RNA-Seq	Alzheimer's Disease	436 participants	https://www.nature.com/articles/s41467-020-19622-y	Strong FAIR compliance with local data access protocols and well-documented methodology through published manuscript. Study uses standardized RNA-Seq data from established cohorts (ROSMAP and MayoRNAseq) available through the AD Knowledge Portal, employing standardized data collection protocols and computational methods for disease progression modeling. Data access requires formal procedures through source repositories, with comprehensive documentation of analysis methods and biological validation.	2026-01-01 00:00:00	Mette/Pietro	['https://www.nature.com/articles/s41467-020-19622-y']	Study			
The Religious Orders Study and Memory and Aging Project iPSC-Derived Induced Neurons Study	ROSMAP-IN	clinical, proteomics, transcriptomics, genetics	Clinical assessments; TMT proteomics; Whole transcriptome RNA sequencing; Gene expression; iPSC-derived induced neurons	Alzheimer's Disease	12 lines, multiple iPSC lines derived from ROSMAP cohort participants across spectrum of AD pathologies	https://doi.org/10.1016/j.neuron.2021.08.003	Strong FAIR compliance with detailed methodological documentation, standardized TMT proteomics and transcriptomics protocols, integration with parent ROSMAP clinical and neuropathological data, and comprehensive metadata schemas. Local data access via remote repository indicates controlled access procedures with quality control measures and reproducible processing pipelines documented in published protocol.	2026-01-01 00:00:00	Mette/Pietro	['https://doi.org/10.1016/j.neuron.2021.08.003']	Study			
The Seattle Alzheimer's Disease Brain Cell Atlas (SEA-AD) Study	SEA-AD	clinical, genetics, epigenomics, transcriptomics	Clinical assessments; Cognitive assessments; Neuropathology; Genomic variants; Single-nucleus RNA sequencing; Single-nucleus ATAC sequencing; Multiome (gene expression and chromatin accessibility)	Alzheimer's Disease; Mild Cognitive Impairment; Normal aging controls	89 participants	https://portal.brain-map.org/explore/seattle-alzheimers-disease	Excellent FAIR compliance. The SEA-AD study demonstrates exceptional commitment to open science with data publicly available through the Allen Brain Map portal and dedicated study website (https://sea-ad.org/). Findability is excellent with comprehensive documentation, published datasets with DOIs, and indexing in major repositories. Accessibility is strong with open data portals, multiple access methods (web browser, API, bulk download), and well-documented procedures. Interoperability is high through use of standard genomics file formats (BAM, h5ad, MEX), metadata following community standards, and integration with the Brain Cell Data Center. Reusability is maximized through comprehensive metadata documentation, detailed published protocols, quality control metrics, and clear data use guidelines. The multi-modal integration of clinical, neuropathology, genomics, epigenomics, and single-cell transcriptomics data creates a rich, standardized resource for the research community.	2026-01-01 00:00:00	Mette/Pietro	['https://portal.brain-map.org/explore/seattle-alzheimers-disease']	Study			
The single nucleus RNA sequencing analysis of TREM2-impact in Alzheimer's Disease study	snRNAseqAD_TREM2	clinical, transcriptomics	Clinical; Single nucleus RNA sequencing; Gene Expression	Alzheimer's Disease	32 participants	https://www.nature.com/articles/s41591-019-0695-9#Sec45	Strong FAIR compliance with local data access through established repository (ROSMAP cohort), comprehensive metadata documentation including TREM2 variant stratification (TREM2-CV, TREM2-R62H, controls), standardized single-nucleus RNA-seq protocols generating 66,311 profiles from prefrontal cortex, and associated peer-reviewed publication in Nature Medicine providing detailed methodology and data description, though direct open data portal access not specified.	2026-01-01 00:00:00	Mette/Pietro	['https://www.nature.com/articles/s41591-019-0695-9#Sec45']	Study			
Whitehall II Study	Whitehall-II	clinical, longitudinal	Occupational cohort; Cognitive testing; Health behaviors; Social factors; Quality of life measures	Cognitive Decline; Dementia; Cardiovascular Disease; Aging	10,308 participants	https://www.ucl.ac.uk/epidemiology-health-care/research/epidemiology-and-public-health/research/whitehall-ii	Excellent FAIR compliance with long-running occupational cohort study	2025-12-01 00:00:00	Mette/Pietro	['https://www.ucl.ac.uk/epidemiology-health-care/research/epidemiology-and-public-health/research/whitehall-ii']	Study			
